k back in to trad leading again.&nbsp;</span><span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: initial;">The route was </span><a href="http://gregboswell.co.uk/index.php/2012/11/27/snow-its-scary-stuff/" style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: initial;">first climbed</a><span style="-webkit-text-stroke-width: initial;"> by Greg Boswell and Guy Robertson in 2012. All four pitches were really good fun, with mostly positive hooks, especially where you really need it. In fact, I got my tools stuck in the crack twice on pitch one!</span></div><div style="-webkit-text-stroke-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); -webkit-text-stroke-width: initial; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 11px; line-height: normal; min-height: 13px;"><span style="font-kerning: none;"></span><br /></div><br /><div style="-webkit-text-stroke-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); -webkit-text-stroke-width: initial; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 11px; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-kerning: none;">The highlight of the day was the lovely moonlight as we abseiled back down. The Ben is a little worrying right now, with a lot of loose blocks which are not keyed-in as they normally would be since itâ€™s been both very dry and snowless this winter so far. It still feels like November up there.</span></div><div style="-webkit-text-stroke-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); -webkit-text-stroke-width: initial; font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 11px; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-kerning: none;"><br /></span></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-d6XrJ7_h06Q/WJheh0Lra5I/AAAAAAAAEN0/BidZmOGnnKUBcXGJRluTbBaNVywhpbaAACLcB/s1600/%253Cuntitled%253E%2B2.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="640" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-d6XrJ7_h06Q/WJheh0Lra5I/AAAAAAAAEN0/BidZmOGnnKUBcXGJRluTbBaNVywhpbaAACLcB/s640/%253Cuntitled%253E%2B2.jpg" width="425" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div cl